# GitHub Personal Access Token (PAT)
# Create a real token at https://github.com/settings/tokens ( fine‑grained token with Contents Read/Write )
# Paste the token on the line below (no quotes, no extra spaces)
YOUR_GITHUB_PAT_HERE

# Security notes:
# - Set file permissions: chmod 600 github_token.txt
# - Never commit this file to version control (it is gitignored)
# - Use this token for pushing the sovereignty‑suite repo only; do not reuse for other services
# - Rotate the token every 90 days or if you suspect compromise
